CAP

	1.Consistency  (Gives same data to both servers)
	2.Availability (Database should response according to query)
	3.Partition Tolerance 
		- Scaling
			1. Horizontal scaling
			2. Vertical Scaling
	 One database is present in EUROPE and one is present in India
	 If change is made in Indian database and by chance connection gets lost then European database doesnt get updated
	 Basically handling synchronisation is known as partition tolerance

 
	=> Agar 2 valid hai to teesra valid nhi ho sakta acc to cap theorem (consistent , available hai to partition tolerance nhi hoga)
	

PACELC(Extended version of Cap)

	if(partition)
		Availability or consistency

	else 
		Latency or Consistency

	Partition hai to cap theorem ki tarah work karega else
	latency ya consistency suffer karenge
	Latency matlb data update karne k liye kuch time lagega(Query queue ho jati hai jb disk free hoti hai tb kaam hota hai actual mei so time lag hota hai)

Families of DataBases		

1.Acid
	Atomic
	Consistent
	Isolated	
	Durable

2.Base
	Basically available
	Soft State
	Eventually consistent
	
Agar 4 rows update kar rahe ho and by chance power na ho aur sirf 2 h update ho payi ho to hum prefer karte hai ki wo 2 jo write hui ho wo bh undo ho jaye
Isliye copy bnti hai original ki aur agar updated wali sahi se update na ho paye to purana copy wale se restore ho jata hai 

Base aur Acid opp hai ek dusre ke 

Agar consistent hai to basically available nhi hogi

Eventually consistent ka matlb ye hai ki har nayi query k liye wo bolega update ho gaya hai but actual me tab update hoga jb queue empty ho


